# Cloud Functions for Firebase

Cloud Functions for Firebase (2nd gen) run serverless backend code in response to events from Firebase services and HTTP requests. Functions are built on Cloud Run and scale automatically from zero.

## Project Structure

```
my-app/
├── firebase.json             # Deploy targets — "functions" config
├── .firebaserc               # Project aliases
├── functions/
│   ├── package.json          # Dependencies (firebase-functions, firebase-admin)
│   ├── tsconfig.json         # TypeScript config
│   ├── .env                  # Environment variables (non-secret)
│   ├── .secret.local         # Secrets for emulator
│   └── src/
│       └── index.ts          # Entry point — all exports become deployed functions
```

## Initialize Functions

```bash
firebase init functions
# Select: TypeScript
# Creates: functions/ directory with package.json, tsconfig.json, src/index.ts
```

## HTTP Function (onRequest)

```typescript
// functions/src/index.ts
import { onRequest } from "firebase-functions/v2/https";

export const api = onRequest((req, res) => {
  const name = req.query.name || "World";
  res.json({ message: `Hello, ${name}!` });
});
```

Deploys to: `https://<region>-<project>.cloudfunctions.net/api`

## Callable Function (onCall)

```typescript
import { onCall, HttpsError } from "firebase-functions/v2/https";

export const addMessage = onCall((request) => {
  // request.auth is automatically populated from client SDK
  if (!request.auth) {
    throw new HttpsError("unauthenticated", "Must be logged in");
  }

  const text = request.data.text;
  const uid = request.auth.uid;

  // Write to Firestore, process data, etc.
  return { result: `Message from ${uid}: ${text}` };
});
```

Client invocation:

```typescript
import { getFunctions, httpsCallable } from "firebase/functions";
const functions = getFunctions();
const addMessage = httpsCallable(functions, "addMessage");
const result = await addMessage({ text: "Hello" });
```

## Firestore Trigger

```typescript
import { onDocumentCreated } from "firebase-functions/v2/firestore";

export const onUserCreated = onDocumentCreated("users/{userId}", (event) => {
  const snapshot = event.data;
  if (!snapshot) return;

  const userData = snapshot.data();
  console.log(`New user: ${event.params.userId}`, userData);

  // Send welcome email, create profile, etc.
  return snapshot.ref.update({ welcomeEmailSent: true });
});
```

Other Firestore triggers:

```typescript
import {
  onDocumentUpdated,
  onDocumentDeleted,
  onDocumentWritten,
} from "firebase-functions/v2/firestore";

export const onProfileUpdated = onDocumentUpdated("profiles/{profileId}", (event) => {
  const before = event.data?.before.data();
  const after = event.data?.after.data();
  console.log(`Profile changed from`, before, `to`, after);
});

export const onPostDeleted = onDocumentDeleted("posts/{postId}", (event) => {
  const deletedData = event.data?.data();
  console.log(`Post deleted:`, deletedData);
});

export const onOrderWritten = onDocumentWritten("orders/{orderId}", (event) => {
  // Fires on create, update, and delete
  const before = event.data?.before.data(); // undefined on create
  const after = event.data?.after.data();   // undefined on delete
});
```

## Auth Trigger

```typescript
import { onAuthUserCreated, onAuthUserDeleted } from "firebase-functions/v2/identity";

export const welcomeNewUser = onAuthUserCreated((event) => {
  const user = event.data;
  console.log(`New user signed up: ${user.uid}, email: ${user.email}`);
  // Create user profile, send welcome email, etc.
});

export const cleanupDeletedUser = onAuthUserDeleted((event) => {
  const user = event.data;
  console.log(`User deleted: ${user.uid}`);
  // Clean up user data across collections
});
```

## Storage Trigger

```typescript
import { onObjectFinalized } from "firebase-functions/v2/storage";

export const processUpload = onObjectFinalized((event) => {
  const filePath = event.data.name;          // "uploads/photo.jpg"
  const contentType = event.data.contentType; // "image/jpeg"
  const fileSize = event.data.size;           // bytes
  const bucket = event.data.bucket;

  console.log(`File uploaded: gs://${bucket}/${filePath}`);

  if (!contentType?.startsWith("image/")) {
    console.log("Not an image, skipping.");
    return;
  }

  // Generate thumbnail, scan for content, update metadata, etc.
});
```

## Scheduled Function

```typescript
import { onSchedule } from "firebase-functions/v2/scheduler";

export const dailyCleanup = onSchedule("every day 02:00", async (event) => {
  console.log("Running daily cleanup...");
  // Delete expired records, send digest emails, etc.
});

export const frequentSync = onSchedule("every 5 minutes", async (event) => {
  console.log("Running sync...");
});

// Cron syntax also works
export const weeklyReport = onSchedule("0 9 * * 1", async (event) => {
  console.log("Generating weekly report...");
});
```

## Environment Config and Secrets

```typescript
import { defineSecret, defineString, defineInt } from "firebase-functions/params";

// Secrets — stored in Google Secret Manager, injected at runtime
const stripeKey = defineSecret("STRIPE_SECRET_KEY");
const openaiKey = defineSecret("OPENAI_API_KEY");

// Parameterized config — prompted during deploy or set in .env
const appName = defineString("APP_NAME", { default: "My App" });
const maxRetries = defineInt("MAX_RETRIES", { default: 3 });

export const processPayment = onRequest(
  { secrets: [stripeKey] },  // Declare which secrets the function needs
  (req, res) => {
    const key = stripeKey.value();  // Access the secret value
    res.json({ app: appName.value(), retries: maxRetries.value() });
  }
);
```

```bash
# Set secrets
firebase functions:secrets:set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
# Prompts for value, stores in Google Secret Manager

# Set .env variables (non-secret)
# functions/.env
APP_NAME=My Production App
MAX_RETRIES=5

# functions/.env.local (emulator only)
APP_NAME=My Dev App
```

## Function Options

```typescript
import { onRequest } from "firebase-functions/v2/https";

export const heavyApi = onRequest(
  {
    region: "us-central1",        // Set region explicitly
    memory: "1GiB",               // 128MiB to 32GiB
    timeoutSeconds: 300,           // Up to 3600 (60 min) for v2
    minInstances: 1,               // Keep warm — avoid cold starts
    maxInstances: 100,             // Limit scaling
    concurrency: 80,               // Requests per instance (v2 only)
    cors: true,                    // Enable CORS
  },
  (req, res) => {
    res.json({ status: "ok" });
  }
);
```

## Deployment

```bash
# Deploy all functions
firebase deploy --only functions

# Deploy a specific function
firebase deploy --only functions:api

# Deploy multiple specific functions
firebase deploy --only functions:api,functions:onUserCreated

# View deployed functions
firebase functions:list

# Delete a function
firebase functions:delete api --region us-central1

# View function logs
firebase functions:log --only api
```

## Emulator

```bash
# Start functions emulator (with Firestore, Auth, Storage)
firebase emulators:start --only functions

# Start all emulators
firebase emulators:start

# Functions emulator runs on port 5001 by default
# Test HTTP functions: curl http://localhost:5001/<project>/<region>/api
```

## v2 Import Paths

| Trigger Type | Import Path |
|-------------|-------------|
| HTTP / Callable | `firebase-functions/v2/https` |
| Firestore | `firebase-functions/v2/firestore` |
| Auth | `firebase-functions/v2/identity` |
| Storage | `firebase-functions/v2/storage` |
| Scheduled | `firebase-functions/v2/scheduler` |
| Pub/Sub | `firebase-functions/v2/pubsub` |
| Alerts | `firebase-functions/v2/alerts` |
| Params / Config | `firebase-functions/params` |
